Leaping																CATEGORY:Power		TYPE:Power					PREVARGTEQ:Power_Point_Pool,1+LeapingPowerCost		DESC:You can make prodigious leaps, far more than even a skilled athlete. Your Leaping rank, minus 2, is the distance rank you cover in a single standing jump: so 15 feet at rank 1, 30 feet at rank 2, up to 1,000 miles at rank 20! You do not suffer any damage from landing after a jump, so long as it is within your maximum distance. The speed rank of your leap maxes out at 7 (around 250 miles per hour), so leaps of greater than distance rank 7 take time equal to the distance rank minus 7. For example, a massive leap of 500 miles (distance rank 17) takes time rank 10 (17 - 7, or two hours) of time in the air! Because of this, leapers may choose to make shorter "hops" of just a couple miles, leaving them airborne for only a minute or so, to better control their direction.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								BONUS:VAR|Power_Point_Pool|-1+LeapingPowerCost			COST:0				ASPECT:Power Type|Movement	ASPECT:Action|Free	ASPECT:Range|Personal	ASPECT:Duration|Instant	ASPECT:Cost|1 point per rank

